  "chapter": {
    "number": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel Will Reap the Whirlwind"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the ram’s horn to your lips!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "An eagle looms over the house of the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because the people have transgressed My covenant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rebelled against My law.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel cries out to Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“O our God, we know You!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But Israel has rejected good;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "an enemy will pursue him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They set up kings, but not by Me.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They make princes, but without My approval.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "With their silver and gold they make themselves idols,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to their own destruction.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has rejected your calf,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2483
          },
          {
            "text": "O Samaria.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My anger burns against them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "How long will they be",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "incapable of innocence?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For this thing is from Israel—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a craftsman made it, and it is not God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It will be broken to pieces,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that calf of Samaria.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they sow the wind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they shall reap the whirlwind.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "There is no standing grain;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "what sprouts fails to yield flour.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Even if it should produce,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the foreigners would swallow it up.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel is swallowed up!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Now they are among the nations",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like a worthless vessel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they have gone up to Assyria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a wild donkey on its own.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Ephraim",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2484
          },
          {
            "text": "has hired lovers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though they hire allies among the nations,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will now round them up,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will begin to diminish",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "under the oppression of the king of princes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though Ephraim multiplied the altars for sin,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they became his altars for sinning.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though I wrote for them the great things of My law,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they regarded them as something strange.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though they offer sacrifices as gifts to Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and though they eat the meat,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD does not accept them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Now He will remember their iniquity and punish their sins:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They will return to Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel has forgotten his Maker and built palaces;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Judah has multiplied its fortified cities.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But I will send fire upon their cities,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and it will consume their citadels.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
